videos.description: Tigers quarterback Drew Lock gets sacked by the Wildcats' Josh Allen, forcing a fumble which is recovered by the Wildcats at their own 20.
videos.headline: Missouri QB has costly fumble

videos.description: Stephen Johnson connects with an open Blake Bone for a 14-yard touchdown to give Kentucky an early lead over Missouri.
videos.headline: Kentucky takes the lead with TD

videos.description: Missouri's DeMarkus Acy is ejected from the game for a helmet-to-helmet targeting call when he collides with Kentucky's Lynn Bowden.
videos.headline: Missouri DB ejected on targeting

videos.description: Kayaune Ross breaks several tackles on a 17-yard run that would result in a field goal to add to Kentucky's lead.
videos.headline: Ross run gets Wildcats closer to FG

videos.description: Drew Lock finds J'Mon Moore for 50 yards and the touchdown to get Missouri on the board.
videos.headline: Moore streaks for 50-yard TD

videos.description: Benny Snell Jr. stiff-arms a tackler and tip toes the sideline in his impressive 71-yard rushing touchdown to strengthen the Wildcats' lead.
videos.headline: Snell burst down the field for 71-yard TD

videos.description: Drew Lock goes deep and finds a wide open Emanuel Hall for a 58-yard touchdown to close the gap before halftime.
videos.headline: Tigers chip away at lead with deep TD

videos.description: Kentucky head coach Mark Stoops breaks down what his team has worked for his team and what has to improve coming the second half.
videos.headline: Stoops: We just got to keep playing

videos.description: Missouri coach Barry Odom wants to see team score more in this half and keep defense fresh.
videos.headline: Odom is impressed with the momentum Missouri

videos.description: Benny Snell Jr. rushes for 6-yard touchdown scoring the Wildcats first touchdown of the second half.
videos.headline: Snell rushes for second TD

videos.description: Drew Lock finds a gap and rushes into the end zone to bring with Tigers within three.
videos.headline: Lock rushes 1-yard TD for Tigers

videos.description: Stephen Johnson connects with Garrett Johnson for 64-yard touchdown to give the Wildcats the lead once again.
videos.headline: Johnson reclaims lead for Kentucky

videos.description: Missouri quarterback Drew Lock goes deep to find a wide-open Johnathon Johnson for a 75 yard touchdown to tie Kentucky.
videos.headline: Missouri ties game with 75-yard TD

videos.description: Kentucky coach Mark Stoops lays out how proud he is of his team and how essential Stephen Johnson was to Saturday's victory.
videos.headline: Stoops is 'very pleased' with win

videos.description: Kentucky's Stephen Johnson discusses why the team needs to keep playing the way they did Saturday and keep the momentum going.
videos.headline: Johnson: We just kept fighting

videos.description: Andre Ware and Taylor Zarzour break down Kentucky's victory and the progress that Missouri has made even though they lost.
videos.headline: Kentucky keeps finding ways to win
